NEWS file for package baseline
Collection of baseline correction algorithms, along with a framework and a GUI for optimising baseline algorithm parameters.
Kristian Hovde Liland and BjÃ¸rn-Helge Mevik, Norway

##### Version 1.3-4
Date: 6 July 2022
>> Corrected plotOptim routine and added optimisation example.

##### Version 1.3-3
Date: 26 November 2021
>> Minor updates in documentation.

##### Version 1.3-2
Date: 22 September 2021
>> Minor updates in documentation.

##### Version 1.3-1
Date: 10 September 2020
>> Updated graphical user interface with visible slider values and fixed bug for handling multiple spectra.

##### Version 1.3-0
Date: 10 May 2020
>> Changed graphical user interface to use gWidgets2 and its gWidgets2tcltk.

##### Version 1.2-2
Date: 04 November 2019
>> Added TAP correction for baseline identification in kinetic anlaysis of derivative kinetic data. Converted package to UTF-8.

##### Version 1.2-0
Date: 11 March 2015
>> Added Shirley background correction for X-ray Photoelectron Spectroscopy.

##### Version 1.1-2
Date: 02 May 2013
>> Fixed bug in environment setting (tip from Tom Wenseleers).

##### Version 1.1-1
Date: 27 March 2013
>> Fixed bug concerning naming of methods in the user interfaces (tip from Tom Wenseleers).
>> Minor changes to conform to new rules concerning assigning variables to the global environment.

##### Version 1.1-0
Date: 24 June 2012
>> Open up for user extensions of baseline algorithms for plotting and optimisation through different
use of the list baselineAlgorithms.
>> Added list baselineAlgorithmsGUI for setting up graphical user interface with baseline algorithms
included in the baselineAglrithms list.
